						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Keebler wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">In regards to name table mirroring: If I were to disable the internal 2k CIRAM and provide 4k on the cart to use instead so that all name tables have their own area in memory, would games that utilize horizontal or vertical mirroring still work?</div><br />Some will, some won't, depends on how the game was programmed. When I'm programming, I often try to make my software 4-screen friendly, as long as there is no big performance hit.<br /><br />If you want to try it out, FCEUXD lets you change the mirroring type on the fly on the name table viewer. However, if the game uses a mapper than can control the mirroring and it's changed all the time, you can't really select another mirroring because it's constantly set to what the game wants.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Keebler wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Why is the base limit without a mapper on CHR-ROM size 8k? From the schematic it looks as though the NES can actually address 16k work of CHR-ROM via A0-A13.</div>
<br />Probably because there is no way to index more than 256 background tiles and 256 sprite tiles with 8-bit indexes.</div>

					
