						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Your idea of using the attribute bits for selecting CHR banks is quite interesting.</div><br />I sort of got the idea from <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Texas_Instruments_TMS9918#Screen_modes" class="postlink">Mode 1 (Graphic 1) of TMS9918</a>, as well as how the MMC5 handles certain things.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">There are also 3 unused bits in the attribute byte of the sprites which they could have used to select banks.</div>
