					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The PPU does address 16kB.  I know when I used a 32kB RAM chip for my CHR setup on Squeedo, the palette writes (at $3F00-$3F10) would end up in that same position in the CHR chip, overlapping one of the CHR banks (presumed I would use that bank for BIOS functions, etc.).  BTW, in that case it's just a couple NAND gates to force it to use a certain bank when nametables are active.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

